{"key":"post-12528067","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12528067</id>\n<content>Vermiculite is a pretty good bulk substrate material.&amp;nbsp; The first few growers who discovered this thought that verm was an inert substance and the only benefit was for holding water, as a &lt;i&gt;reservoir&lt;/i&gt;, thus it was named 'rez effect'.&amp;nbsp; We now know that verm contains minerals that are beneficial to fungi, and it can be used as a bulk substrate, either by itself or along with manure or coir, etc.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12528096</next>\n<prev>12527761</prev>\n<first>12527668</first>\n<last>12528997</last>\n<when>1273360597</when>\n<utime>05/09/10 02:16 AM</utime>\n</post>"}